00:33:05.800 --> 00:33:11.800
Val Evans and Inwill Evans, his mother, had a grocery shop and a sweet shop there.

00:33:11.800 --> 00:33:12.800
I remember that, yes.

00:33:12.800 --> 00:33:14.800
That's been many things on the corner.

00:33:14.800 --> 00:33:18.800
And then where Holton's Fish and Chip shop is now,

00:33:18.800 --> 00:33:24.800
Mrs. Evans also had a sweet shop there years ago,

00:33:24.800 --> 00:33:26.800
before she moved to the corner.

00:33:26.800 --> 00:33:28.800
I can remember that as a kid.

00:33:28.800 --> 00:33:30.800
Yes, everybody moves, don't they?

00:33:30.800 --> 00:33:31.800
Yeah, that's right.

00:33:31.800 --> 00:33:33.800
They set up somewhere else.

00:33:33.800 --> 00:33:34.800
Yes.

00:33:34.800 --> 00:33:41.800
I can remember Dr. Poole used to live, had his surgery at home at Brinkoid,

00:33:42.800 --> 00:33:50.800
by the car park, and they used to take maternity patients in, didn't they?

00:33:50.800 --> 00:33:53.800
Yes, yes, several people.

00:33:53.800 --> 00:33:54.800
Yes, we used to go there.

00:33:54.800 --> 00:33:56.800
Well, we were actually four there, yes.

00:33:56.800 --> 00:33:58.800
And they used to keep goats.

00:33:58.800 --> 00:34:01.800
And if these goats got out, they'd chase you, you know.

00:34:01.800 --> 00:34:04.800
And I can remember going down to the dark place,

00:34:04.800 --> 00:34:06.800
we were terrified that these goats might be out.

00:34:06.800 --> 00:34:08.800
And I remember this one day, this one was out.

00:34:08.800 --> 00:34:11.800
When I took off down the road with him behind me,

00:34:11.800 --> 00:34:15.800
and I dashed into Mrs. Evans's sweet shop, and they go after me.

00:34:15.800 --> 00:34:20.800
Oh, I don't think that's an element of the chemist, but never mind.

00:34:20.800 --> 00:34:22.800
Just memories of growing up.

00:34:22.800 --> 00:34:24.800
It doesn't happen these days.

00:34:24.800 --> 00:34:26.800
The name of the farm was Dolvea.

00:34:26.800 --> 00:34:29.800
That's where we stayed, a little farmhouse.

00:34:29.800 --> 00:34:33.800
So we shared the house with another family.

00:34:34.800 --> 00:34:40.800
I can remember my mother, the other lady that lived there,

00:34:40.800 --> 00:34:45.800
they used to cycle to town for milk, you know, every so often.

00:34:45.800 --> 00:34:47.800
They'd take it in turns to do that.

00:34:47.800 --> 00:34:52.800
So we certainly moved around.

00:34:52.800 --> 00:34:54.800
Dolvea, did you say?

00:34:54.800 --> 00:34:56.800
B-Y-R?

00:34:56.800 --> 00:34:57.800
D-O-L.

00:34:57.800 --> 00:34:59.800
F-I-R, I think it did.

00:34:59.800 --> 00:35:02.800
Well, we look at it on the map anyway.

00:35:02.800 --> 00:35:04.800
Dolvea, it is, yeah.

00:35:04.800 --> 00:35:06.800
Down the Pound Lane, was it?

00:35:06.800 --> 00:35:12.800
Yeah, you can go in from the main road and turn by...

00:35:12.800 --> 00:35:14.800
Down towards Teylettice there.

00:35:14.800 --> 00:35:17.800
That's right, yeah, you turn up the lane there.

00:35:17.800 --> 00:35:19.800
We find it on the map.

00:35:19.800 --> 00:35:21.800
I don't remember living there.

00:35:21.800 --> 00:35:23.800
I was only a little kid, I expect.

00:35:23.800 --> 00:35:26.800
What do you remember of school?

00:35:26.800 --> 00:35:28.800
I can't remember a lot of it.

00:35:28.800 --> 00:35:30.800
I know I went to Cuntighver School.

00:35:30.800 --> 00:35:34.800
And the only thing I can really remember of Cuntighver School,

00:35:34.800 --> 00:35:38.800
that on your birthday, whoever was in the class had a birthday

00:35:38.800 --> 00:35:40.800
the same day as you.

00:35:40.800 --> 00:35:42.800
You had to sit on a chair with them,

00:35:42.800 --> 00:35:45.800
and there was a lantern down Cuntighver somewhere,

00:35:45.800 --> 00:35:49.800
and he sat by my side, and I wasn't very pleased.

00:35:49.800 --> 00:35:52.800
I don't know why.

00:35:52.800 --> 00:35:54.800
There we are.

00:35:54.800 --> 00:35:56.800
That's all I can remember about Cuntighver School.

00:35:56.800 --> 00:35:59.800
Then I went to Reader School.

00:35:59.800 --> 00:36:03.800
And I think I was taught by...

00:36:05.800 --> 00:36:08.800
Mr. Price.

00:36:08.800 --> 00:36:11.800
Miss Farmer.

00:36:12.800 --> 00:36:16.800
And Mrs. Owen.

00:36:16.800 --> 00:36:19.800
She used to live at Glance Earth, or she left,

00:36:19.800 --> 00:36:23.800
she was at Glance Earth, but she was on Glyfran before that.

00:36:23.800 --> 00:36:26.800
I can remember that.

00:36:26.800 --> 00:36:28.800
I don't remember.

00:36:28.800 --> 00:36:30.800
Oh, and Miss Farmer.

00:36:30.800 --> 00:36:32.800
If you didn't bring your sewing to school,

00:36:32.800 --> 00:36:35.800
which they did sewing in those days, you know, embroidery,

00:36:35.800 --> 00:36:39.800
she'd make you down her brother's socks.

00:36:39.800 --> 00:36:43.800
I'm quite a good downer, actually.

00:36:43.800 --> 00:36:45.800
Oh, well.

00:36:45.800 --> 00:36:48.800
And is that where you got interested in knitting?

00:36:48.800 --> 00:36:52.800
No, I think my mother taught me to knit.

00:36:52.800 --> 00:36:54.800
And I think I got...

00:36:54.800 --> 00:36:58.800
Jennifer's a good bit younger than me, my younger sister.

00:36:58.800 --> 00:37:01.800
I used to knit for our dresser dolls.

00:37:01.800 --> 00:37:03.800
So that's how I came about it.

00:37:03.800 --> 00:37:05.800
But I still do knit, you know.

00:37:05.800 --> 00:37:07.800
I just finished a show now.

00:37:07.800 --> 00:37:09.800
You are a wonderful knitter.

00:37:09.800 --> 00:37:14.800
You know, I made a real mess up of that, because not mess up.

00:37:14.800 --> 00:37:19.800
I was counting the amounts, I suppose I had 143 patterns on this show.

00:37:19.800 --> 00:37:23.800
And I think I've done about 50 too many.

00:37:23.800 --> 00:37:25.800
That's all I do.

00:37:25.800 --> 00:37:27.800
I don't want to do that.

00:37:27.800 --> 00:37:30.800
You've won so many prizes in shows and competitions, haven't you?

00:37:30.800 --> 00:37:32.800
Absolutely wonderful.

00:37:32.800 --> 00:37:34.800
Do you want to see the one I do?

